  characterSystem:
    characterName: Robert Left
    hejFras: 'Hello there, champ! '
    hejFrasEvent:
      Guid:
        Data1: -2104060913
        Data2: 1209689446
        Data3: 54907323
        Data4: -1217176902
      Path: event:/Robert/Robert Hej
    firstQuestion:
      question: 'Interesting duds you have there! '
      answer: "I\u2019m dressed for the skies! I\u2019m New York's finest pilot!
        Hot Airballoon Pilot that is. "
    q1FollowUpQuestion1:
      question: 'Flying in a balloon? That sounds dangerous! '
      answer: "Oh it certainly is. There\u2019s nothing I fear more than the ground,
        quickly coming towards you! But my love for flight trumps any fear! "
    q1FollowUpQuestion2:
      question: 'Amazing! Where do you park a balloon in New York? '
      answer: "Well I parked it on the roof of this building. Hope Mr. Allford doesn\u2019t
        mind\u2026 I\u2019ve heard some scary rumors about that fellow\u2026"
    secondQuestion:
      question: 'You look a bit uncomfortable there. '
      answer: "I seem to have gotten sand in my stompers! I would pour it out right
        here and now, but it doesn\u2019t seem proper. "
    q2FollowUpQuestion1:
      question: 'Where do you find sand on a hot air balloon? '
      answer: "In the ballast of course, the big bags on the side! People here seem
        to have very limited knowledge about aviation technology\u2026 "
    q2FollowUpQuestion2:
      question: 'You sound disappointed? '
      answer: "Well, you see, the main reason I went to this ball was to coerce some\u2026
        glitterati\u2026 to invest in my inventions! Though it seems like many are
        preoccupied with the rumors about Mr. Allford. It seems like my plan is going
        belly up\u2026"
    thirdQuestion:
      question: "I didn\u2019t see you at the toast? "
      answer: "Oh, well, I arrived a bit late\u2026 You see, I\u2019m a bit of a
        chronic oversleeper. Alarm clocks these days are too quiet! I need something
        to really rattle me awake in the morning! "
    q3FollowUpQuestion1:
      question: "Why don\u2019t you invent something? "
      answer: "Eureka! That\u2019s it! I\u2019ll make the best alarm clock this side
        of the Mississippi! Thank you my friend, I\u2019ll give you some of the profit
        from our brainchild when I\u2019m rich. Hot diggity dog! "
    q3FollowUpQuestion2:
      question: 'Is there something more that you want to give me? '
      answer: "Eeee\u2026 chucks\u2026 I c-could give you an alarm clock for free? "
    "hejD\xE5Fras": Soar long!
